      • getTNanos

        public final long getTNanos​()
        Returns:
        An instant (a pair (startNanos, elapsedNanos), see RateMeter) at which the reading was taken. The more specific semantics may depend on the semantics of the RateMeter's method via which the reading was made and/or on the implementation details.

      • getValueLong

        public final long getValueLong​()
        Returns:
        long representation of the value read. Either rounded, or not. Note that even if the reading is not rounded, this value may not be equal to getValueDouble() because not every long value can be exactly represented as double value.

      • getValueDouble

        public final double getValueDouble​()
        Returns:
        double representation of the value read. Note that even if the reading is not rounded, this value may not be equal to getValueLong() because not every long value can be exactly represented as double value.

      • isRounded

        public final boolean isRounded​()
        Returns:
        A flag that specifies whether getValueLong() returns a rounded representation of getValueDouble(), or not.

      • isAccurate

        public final boolean isAccurate​()
